## 🎬 Scene 2: Setup & Configuration — `git init`, `git config`

### Nayi Project Ka Janma

Raj ne apna pehla project folder banaya:

```bash
# Folder banao
mkdir my-startup-project
cd my-startup-project

# Git ko initialize karo
git init
```

Terminal ne bola: `Initialized empty Git repository in /path/to/my-startup-project/.git`

### Apna Identity Set Karo

"Bhai, tu kaun hai? Teri commit kisme likhaun?" — Git ne poochha.

Raj ne jhatz se apna info diya:

```bash
# Globally set karo (ek baar set, sab projects mein kaam aayega)
git config --global user.name "Raj Kumar"
git config --global user.email "raj@startup.com"

# Specific project ke liye (optional)
git config user.name "Raj Kumar"
git config user.email "raj@startup.com"

# Sab settings dekho
git config --list
git config --global --list

# Kisi bhi specific setting check karo
git config user.name
```

Raj bola: "Done! Ab main Git ke liye tayyar hoon!"

