## 📝 Scene 3: Pehli File aur Status Check — `git status`, `git add`

### File Banate Hain

Raj ne project mein ek HTML file banayee:

```bash
# File create karo (manually bana sakta hai ya terminal se)
touch index.html
echo "<h1>Hello World</h1>" > index.html

# Ya ek README banaate hain
echo "# Mera Pehla Project" > README.md
```

### Git Ko Poocho — Kya Change Hua?

```bash
git status
```

Git ne dikhaaya:
```
On branch main

No commits yet

Untracked files:
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
        index.html
        README.md

nothing added to commit but untracked files present (tracking what will be committed)
```

Raj: "Ohhh! Toh ye files Git ne abhi nahi dekhe? Inhe **staging area** mein daalna padega!"

### Files Ko Staging Area Mein Daalo

```bash
# Specific file add karo
git add index.html

# Ya sab files ek saath
git add .
git add -A

# Kya staged hai check karo
git status
```

Ab `git status` ne dikhaaya:
```
Changes to be committed:
  (use "git rm --cached <file>..." to unstage)
        new file:   index.html
        new file:   README.md
```

