## 🌐 Scene 7: Remote Se Dosti — GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket

### Remote Repository Kya Hota Hai?

Raj: "Mera code sirf mere computer mein hai. Agar computer crash ho jaye?"

Senior: "Isliye **remote repository** use karte hain — GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket pe upload karte hain!"

### GitHub Pe Repository Banao

Raj ne GitHub par ja ke "New Repository" click kiya aur `my-startup-project` naam diya.

GitHub ne ek URL diya:
```
https://github.com/raj-kumar/my-startup-project.git
```

### Remote Connect Karo

```bash
# Remote add karo
git remote add origin https://github.com/raj-kumar/my-startup-project.git

# Remote ka URL check karo
git remote -v

# Output:
# origin  https://github.com/raj-kumar/my-startup-project.git (fetch)
# origin  https://github.com/raj-kumar/my-startup-project.git (push)

# Multiple remotes add karo
git remote add backup https://github.com/backup-user/my-startup-project.git

# Remote ka info dekho
git remote show origin

# Remote rename karo
git remote rename origin github-repo

# Remote remove karo
git remote remove backup
```

### GitHub Par Upload — `git push`

```bash
# Pehli baar push (new branch ke liye)
git push -u origin main
# -u flag = upstream set karo (default banao)

# Agar upstream pehle se set hai
git push

# Kisi specific branch ko push karo
git push origin feature/login-system

# Saari branches push karo
git push --all

# Tags push karo
git push origin v1.0.0
git push --tags

# Force push (careful! 🚨)
git push -f origin main    # local changes ko remote par overwrite
git push --force-with-lease origin main  # safer option
```

### GitHub Se Download — `git pull`

Raj ke office mein colleague Priya ke sath kaam kar rahe the. Priya ne kuch changes push kiye:

```bash
# Latest changes download karo
git pull
# Ye same hai: git fetch + git merge

# Specific branch se pull karo
git pull origin feature/payment

# Pull with rebase
git pull --rebase
# Rebase ke baad apni changes alag aaj jayengi
```

### `git fetch` vs `git pull`

```bash
# Fetch: sirf download, merge nahi
git fetch origin
# Ab local ka 'origin/main' update ho gaya, par local 'main' nahi

# Check karo kya naya aaya
git log main..origin/main   # Ye commits main mein nahi hain

# Ab merge karo manually
git merge origin/main

# Pull = Fetch + Merge automatically
git pull origin main
```

