## ⏮️ Scene 10: Mistakes Hone Toh Hote Hain — `git reset`, `git revert`, `git restore`

### Scenario 1: Galti Se File Add Ho Gaya!

```bash
# File ko unstage karo (staging area se nikalo)
git reset HEAD index.html
git reset index.html

# Ya newer way
git restore --staged index.html
```

### Scenario 2: Galti Se Changes Kiye, Abhi Commit Nahi Kiya

```bash
# File ko original state mein restore karo
git checkout index.html       # old way

# Ya modern way
git restore index.html

# Saari files
git restore .
```

### Scenario 3: Pehle Wale Commits Wapas Lena Hai

#### Option A: History Se Hatao (Destructive)

```bash
# Last 1 commit wapas lo
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# Last 3 commits wapas lo
git reset --hard HEAD~3

# Specific commit ke baad sab wapas karo
git reset --hard a1b2c3d

# ⚠️ WARNING: sab changes permanently deleted ho jayengi!
```

#### Option B: New Commit Se Fix Karo (Safe)

```bash
# Last commit ko undo karo, par history rakhte huye
git revert HEAD

# Ya specific commit ko revert karo (beech wala bhi)
git revert a1b2c3d

# Multiple commits
git revert HEAD~2..HEAD
```

**Reset ke types:**

```bash
# --soft: changes preserved, staging area mein
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# --mixed: changes preserved, working directory mein (default)
git reset --mixed HEAD~1

# --hard: changes deleted forever
git reset --hard HEAD~1
```

### Scenario 4: Lost Commits Recover Karo

```bash
# Sab kaam ki history dekho (even deleted commits)
git reflog

# Specific commit restore karo
git reset --hard a1b2c3d
```

