## 🌊 Scene 14: Rebase vs Merge — History Ko Clean Rakhna

### Issue: History Messy Ho Gaya!

Raj ke team mein 10-15 developers the. Git history bahut complicated ho gaya!

```
main:     C1 ——— C2 ——————————— C8
               ↓    ↑         ↑
feature1:       ——— C3 ——— C4 ⤴
                      ↓
feature2:             ——— C5 ——— C6
```

### Solution 1: Merge (Multiple Base)

```bash
# Feature branch par
git checkout feature1

# Main mein merge
git merge main
```

**Result:**
```
main:     C1 ——— C2 —— C8
               ↓         ↑
feature1:       ——— C3 ——— C4 ——— C7 (merge commit)
                              ↓
                             C6
```

### Solution 2: Rebase (Linear History)

```bash
# Feature branch par
git checkout feature1

# Main par rebase karo
git rebase main

# Conflicts aayein toh fix karo
# ... manually edit files ...
git add .
git rebase --continue

# Ya abort karo
git rebase --abort
```

**Result:**
```
main:     C1 ——— C2 ——— C8
                             ↑
feature1:                     ——— C3' ——— C4'
```

### Rebase vs Merge

| Aspect | Merge | Rebase |
|--------|-------|--------|
| History | Non-linear | Linear |
| Commits | Preserved | Replayed |
| Best For | Public/shared branches | Local branches |
| Safety | Safe (history intact) | Caution (history rewritten) |

